The President's National Security Council met to discuss the progress made in the fight against ISIL in Iraq and Syria. The President was briefed on the Iraqi-led campaign to liberate Mosul and the efforts to isolate Raqqa in Northern Syria. The US Military has also carried out strikes to remove key ISIL leaders and attack planners. The President was updated on the situation in Aleppo, where the Asad regime, with the support of Russia and Iran, has carried out violence. He instructed his team to work with allies and partners to deescalate the violence, provide humanitarian access, and ensure the safe exit of those trapped in the city if desired.